#### Enable API & create OAuth credentials
- Open Google Cloud Console https://console.cloud.google.com/
- Create or select a Project
- Top-left: Select a project → New Project → give it a name → Create.

- **Enable the Calendar API**
- In Cloud Console, go to APIs & Services → Library.
- Search for Google Calendar API, click it, and click Enable.

- **Configure OAuth consent screen**
- Go to APIs & Services → OAuth consent screen.
- Choose External (for quick testing) → Create.
- App name: e.g. Spring AI Demo.
- User support email: your email.
- Add developer contact email.
- For a test/demo, set Publishing status to Testing.
- Add Test Users: add the Google account email you will authorize with (your email).
- Save.

- **Create OAuth 2.0 credentials**
- Go to APIs & Services → Credentials → Create Credentials → OAuth client ID.
- For Application type choose Desktop app (simple for local dev).
- Name it (e.g. Spring AI Demo - Desktop).
- Click Create.
- Click OK and then Download the JSON — this is your credentials.json. Save it securely.

- **Where to put credentials.json**
- Place it in your project root (or src/main/resources/credentials.json)
- Add to .gitignore.